YOLA – A stalwart of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Honourable Peter R. Fwah, has denied stepping down from the Adamawa Southern Senatorial contest. Speaking to journalists at the Nígerian Union of Journalists (NUJ) Press Secretariat in Yola, Honourable Fwah said he can never step down for anybody under any guises because he is a democrat who believes in free and fair contest. Fwah revealed that he has been a PDP man since the days of former President Goodluck Jonathan so he knows that party well and he has all that is needed to contest for the position of Senate in the Adamawa Southern Senatorial District. -Advertisement- He revealed further that he would represent the Adamawa Southern Senatorial District with a passion to change the lives of the people of the state not only from the zone alone but the entire state. The Senatorial candidate who pulled a large crowds of people during the press conference pointed out that Governor Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri has performed so much in lifting the lives of the people and he deserves people like him who have the requisite knowledge to contribute to the development of Adamawa State under the Fintiri administration. He condemned all rumours in circulation that he has stepped down and assured his supporters that he would never step down for anybody in the Senatorial race. He called on him to disregard frivolous talks going on and that he is not going to step down for anybody.